<subsection xml:id="subsec-net-of-a-cone">
    <title>The net of a cone</title>

    <activity>
        <statement>
            <p>
                <m>\textbf{Work in groups.}</m>
            </p>

            <p>
                <m>\textbf{What you need:}</m> model of a cone and a pair of scissors or cutting tool.
            </p>

            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Examine a cone model like the one shown below.
                        </p>

                        <image width="50%">
                            <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                            <latex-image label="cone1">
                                \begin{tikzpicture}
                                % Draw the entire cone with one uniform color (orange)
                                \fill[orange!30] (-2,0) arc (180:360:2 and 0.7) -- (2,0) arc (0:180:2 and 0.7) -- cycle;
                                \fill[orange!30] (-2,0) -- (0,4) -- (2,0) -- cycle;
                                
                                % Draw the base ellipse
                                \draw[thick] (-2,0) arc (180:360:2 and 0.7);
                                \draw[dashed] (2,0) arc (0:180:2 and 0.7);
                                
                                % Draw the cone's sides
                                \draw[thick] (-2,0) -- (0,4);
                                \draw[thick] (2,0) -- (0,4);
                                \end{tikzpicture}
                            </latex-image>
                            
                        </image>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Does the cone have faces, edges and vertices?
                        </p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Carefully cut the cone along its edges.
                        </p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Lay the cone flat after opening it up.
                        </p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Observe the unfolded model and sketch its shape.
                        </p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>
                            What is the name of this 2D layout?
                        </p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Compare your drawing with those made by other groups. What do you notice?
                        </p>
                    </li>

                </ol>
            </p>
            
        </statement>
    </activity>

    <p>
        <m>\textbf{Key Takeaway}</m>
    </p>

    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p>
                    A cone has <m>2</m> faces. One face is a circle and the other face is a curved surface. A net of a cone is made up of <m>1</m> circle and <m>1</m> sector.
                </p>
            </li>

            <li>
                <p>
                    The net of a cone is a two-dimensional representation of the three-dimensional shape of the cone. 
                    It is made up of the curved surface of the cone laid out flat, so that you can see the shape of the cone. 
                    The net of a cone is useful for visualizing the shape of the cone and for calculating its surface area and volume.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>

